This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as Named Entity Recognition (NER). It also involves the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in the field of NLP. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of a framework that can reason over multiple entities and make decisions based on them, which is a key aspect of AI. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques to train the model. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of neural networks to develop the NE-Reasoner framework. 

Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of a specific interaction-pooling mechanism, which is a common technique used in computer vision tasks.
